{
  "text": "The increase we observed in Canada takes place in a broader context and may result from the combination of many factors. The 20th century was characterized notably by a change in the way psychiatry conceptualized mental health problems. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] 55 Once described by psychoanalytic theories, they are now increasingly seen through a neurobiological lens. This may have resulted in an ",
